# Wargio — Arsitektur & Data

## Alur Sistem

```
User (Bahasa Indonesia) → Next.js Frontend → POST /api/chat
→ FastAPI (Cloud Run) → Google Cloud Agent Builder (Gemini 3)
→ MongoDB MCP Server → Atlas (find/aggregate/insertOne/updateOne)
→ Action Engine (restock_alert, debt_summary — post-processing)
```

## Intent → MCP Mapping

Lihat `wargio-intent-mapping.mdc` dan `.cursorules.md` Section 6A.

Write intents (`record_sale`, `record_payment`): konfirmasi user → insertOne/updateOne.
Read intents: find atau aggregate saja.

## Fuzzy Matching

Pipeline: exact alias → partial text (score ≥0.8) → vector search Gemini 768d (score ≥0.85) → disambiguasi max 3 opsi.
Detail: Section 6B `.cursorules.md`.

## Auth MVP

Single warung demo, no login. Session via `X-Session-Id` UUID. Multi-warung out of scope.

## MongoDB Collections

Ikuti schema persis di `.cursorules.md` Section 5:

- `products` — sku, name, name_aliases, category, price_buy/sell, stock_current/minimum, unit, supplier
- `transactions` — type (sale|restock|adjustment), items[], total, payment_method, customer_id
- `customers` — name, phone, debt_total, debt_history[]
- `agent_sessions` — session_id, messages[], context

**Vector Search Index wajib** di Atlas untuk fuzzy product matching (768 dimensions, cosine).

